The best carne asada tacos, ever! Each taco is a meal with the charcoal grilled steak (or chicken, your choice) refried beans, rice and cabbage. Their pico de gallo is spot on and just spicy enough to make the meal complete. There are also many other delicious traditional dishes and tamales for sale as well.There are two locations - Pilsen and Little Village. (Also, Pro tip!) On Saturdays the stores attached to the resturant sell discounted chips, totillas, masa, dried peppers, chicharones (fried pork rinds) and the best nopales salad I have ever tried(and i have tried ALOT)  But You better get there early as it sells out by noon usually. I can only say these tacos are the best and I have been enjoying them for 30 years.
